cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CG, cs.GT

Reasoning: The paper analyzes the computational complexity of various types of puzzles, which involves graph theory, computational complexity, and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also deals with graph algorithms and data structures, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The use of puzzles and constraints to solve problems suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves planar graphs and geometric algorithms, which could place it in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper deals with the mathematical properties of puzzles, which could make it relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
